[32m+[m[32m# OSV (Open Source Vulnerabilities)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mOSV (Open Source Vulnerabilities) is a distributed vulnerability database for open source projects.[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32mIt provides a precise, machine-readable data format (the OSV schema) and an infrastructure to aggregate and serve vulnerability data across multiple ecosystems.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## üîó Quick Links[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Official Website:** https://osv.dev[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Documentation:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - User Guide: https://google.github.io/osv.dev/[m
[32m+[m[32m  - API Reference: https://google.github.io/osv.dev/api/[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Data Dumps:** Available via Google Cloud Storage at `gs://osv-vulnerabilities`[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Learn more: https://osv.dev/docs/#data-dumps[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Mailing List:** https://groups.google.com/g/osv-discuss[m
 [m
